In a conversation between the President and Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu, the President reaffirmed his support for Israel's right to defend itself against rocket attacks. He also welcomed efforts to address intercommunal violence in Jerusalem and urged Israel to protect innocent civilians. The leaders discussed the progress of Israel's military operations against Hamas and other terrorist groups in Gaza. The President expressed support for a ceasefire and discussed US engagement with Egypt and other partners in achieving that goal. Both leaders agreed to maintain close communication with their teams.